  "stimulus_html": "<p>Valganciclovir, marketed as Valcyte, is an antiviral agent used for the treatment of cytomegalovirus. Called a <i>prodrug,</i> valganciclovir is inactive by itself but is rapidly converted in the intestine by hydrolysis of its ester bond to produce an active drug, called ganciclovir, along with an amino acid.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcDhaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--fce1a10ea6540f3475b3841001a00854b28f49fa/OChem_28_EC_009.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of Valganciclovir.\">",
